<!-- +++++++++++ Manifold_subsurface_shape +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Manifold_subsurface_arm.Manifold_subsurface_shape"><p>

A <b>Manifold_subsurface_shape</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/>.
A <b>Manifold_subsurface_shape</b> shall be acyclic.
A <b>Manifold_subsurface_shape</b> shall be in the same geometric context as it's <b>parent_surface</b>.
</p><example>
An example use of <b>Manifold_subsurface_shape</b> is for the case of a  <express_ref linkend="Land:arm:Land_arm.Land"/> shape that contributes to the shape of a  <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Stratum_feature"/>.
</example>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Manifold_subsurface_arm.Manifold_subsurface_shape.parent_surface">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Manifold_subsurface:arm:Manifold_subsurface_arm.open_shell_or_subsurface"/> for the <b>Manifold_subsurface_shape</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Manifold_subsurface_arm.Manifold_subsurface_shape.wr:WR1">
This <b>Manifold_subsurface_shape</b> shall not be <b>parent_surface</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Manifold_subsurface_arm.Manifold_subsurface_shape.wr:WR2">
<p>
<express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model.context_of_items"/> inherited from
<express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/> shall be <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model.context_of_items"/>
for <b>parent_surface</b>.
</p>
</ext_description>

